=================== 27 August, 2018 ===================

**Summary** 
Added feature to [authorize charge](/#authorize-a-charge) by Google Auth instead of phone SMS OTP

1. Call [get account info](/#get-account-info) API to check whether user has enabled Google Auth 2FA from the `google_auth_enabled` flag.

If `google_auth_enabled` is `false`, direct users to [Xfers 2FA setup page](https://www.xfers.io/settings_2fa)

2. Create charge by passing in `user_phone_no`, setting `google_auth` to be `true`.

3. [Authorize charge](/#authorize-a-charge) by passing in `google_auth_code`

